message.content:
2 killers are left in the room. Here's why:

When someone enters the room and kills one of the three killers, there are now only two active killers remaining (the other killer who wasn't killed and another one). The person who entered the room is also considered a killer since they committed an act of killing. Therefore, there are 2 killers left in the room (1 original + 1 new killer - 1 killed).
